HEADWORD: Swanskin
<hw>Swan"skin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of a swan with the down or the feathers on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A species of soft flannel, thick and warm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

